channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: College grads need $99,081 salary offer to change jobs, New York Fed survey says
item.description: The silver lining for employers: Six-figure salary jobs are hard to come by.

item.title: 5 things to know before the stock market opens Wednesday
item.description: Here are the most important news items that investors need to start their trading day.

item.title: Trade and investment data in the last two years dispel the deglobalization and decoupling myths as U.S.-China competition ignites reglobalization
item.description: It's not decoupling or deglobalization, it's reglobalization.

item.title: Mortgage demand from homebuyers drops even as interest rates pull back to April lows
item.description: Total mortgage application volume increased just 0.5% from one week earlier, according to the Mortgage Bankers Association's seasonally adjusted index.

item.title: Africa’s car-making juggernaut prepares to capitalize on global race to produce affordable EVs at scale
item.description: As Europe works to phase out combustion engines over the next decade, automakers like Renault are preparing to adapt in Morocco.

item.title: GameStop, AMC decline as meme stock rally fizzles after just two days
item.description: GameStop and AMC shares fell as the meme stock trading frenzy showed signs of fizzling early on its third day.

item.title: U.K. tax authority HMRC kept Brits on hold for nearly 800 years last fiscal year—and it’s getting worse
item.description: Advisors from HMRC answered just 20.5 million out of 38 million calls between 2022 and 2023.

item.title: Jamie Dimon urges the U.S. to deal with its deficit sooner rather than later
item.description: JPMorgan Chase CEO Jamie Dimon on Wednesday urged the U.S. government to reduce its fiscal deficit sooner rather than later.

item.title: British billionaire Joe Lewis' pilot pleads guilty to tax evasion
item.description: In 2019 Lewis loaned his pilots $500,000 each to buy Mirati shares ahead of the trial results being made public.

item.title: Wednesday's analyst calls: Goldman bullish on Alphabet's AI plans, EV stock gets an upgrade
item.description: Alphabet and a Chinese electric vehicle maker were among the names being talked about by analysts on Wednesday.
